                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <pb n="304"/> LEDHALL. <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Thumel</surname>
                        </persName>', 
               with the assent of his wife and heirs, grants to the <orgName key="org_109039">church and canons regular of St. Frideswide</orgName> 
               in frankalmoigne, the whole of his wood which he has near the wood of 
               <placeName type="minor">Ledhal</placeName>, namely that which extends itself to
               the 'breche' of the abbot of <orgName key="org_109067">Oseney</orgName> towards the south, towards the north as far as
               into the valley (vallem) which is called <placeName type="minor">Widenden</placeName>, and from Widenden, as the way
               extends itself as far as to the oak which is called 'brodehoc,' which stands in the
               middle of the valley of Widenden, and from 'brodehoc,' as the way which is called
               '<placeName type="minor">Esturebroderode</placeName>,' extending itself as far as in 
               'Lacum' which is called 'Harse'.
               (<origDate notBefore="1230" notAfter="1240" precision="low">c. 1230-40</origDate>.) 
                <!--[Wigram no. 893] -->  
               </p>
